4d(A). In the Part C expansion cohort study, patient should meet the following criteria defined in each expansion arm: A. Arm A, pancreatic cancer, ONC-392 monotherapy: a. Histological or cytologically confirmed pancreatic adenocarcinoma that has locally advanced or metastasized (neuroendocrine islet cell neoplasms are excluded). b. With measurable target lesion as determined by RECIST 1.1. c. No more than 2 prior chemotherapy regimens or any other systemic therapy for recurrent/metastatic pancreatic cancer. d. With disease progression following prior 5-FU- or gemcitabine-containing chemotherapy. e. Prior exposure to immunotherapy allowed with a minimum of 28 days washout period. Prior chemotherapy, radiation or target therapy should have a minimum of 21 days washout period. f. Life expectancy ≥ 12 weeks..IEORRES4DA
